---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Peptide Library - our mission, team, and commitment to evidence-based peptide education."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header class="mb-12 relative">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-[var(--primary)]/10 via-transparent to-transparent rounded-2xl -z-10"></div>
      <div class="p-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">About Peptide Library</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-white/80">
          Making peptide research accessible, understandable, and trustworthy.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        Peptide Library exists because understanding peptide research shouldn't require a PhD.
        We believe everyone deserves access to accurate, well-organized scientific information
        to make informed decisions about their health.
      </p>
      <p>
        We synthesize research from peer-reviewed journals, clinical trials, and regulatory
        sources into comprehensive, readable dossiers. Every claim is cited. Every uncertainty
        is acknowledged.
      </p>

      <h2>What Makes Us Different</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-[var(--primary)]/10 to-transparent p-6 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Citation-First</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/70">
            Every factual claim links to a primary source. No vague references to "studies show."
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-500/10 to-transparent p-6 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Evidence Grading</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/70">
            Clear ratings help you understand the quality and strength of available evidence.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-500/10 to-transparent p-6 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Global Coverage</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/70">
            We include international research, not just US-centric sources.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-500/10 to-transparent p-6 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">No Hype</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/70">
            Neutral language. No miracle claims. We tell you what's known and what isn't.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>What We Don't Do</h2>
      <p>
        We're explicit about our boundaries:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>We don't give medical advice.</strong> Consult a healthcare provider for
          personal medical decisions.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We don't provide dosing protocols.</strong> That's between you and your doctor.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We don't recommend sources.</strong> We're not a purchasing guide.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Standards</h2>
      <p>
        Read our <a href="/methodology">Methodology</a> for details on how we research,
        our <a href="/editorial-policy">Editorial Policy</a> for our content standards,
        and our <a href="/advertising-policy">Advertising Policy</a> for how we maintain
        editorial independence.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions, corrections, or feedback? We'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:hello@peptide-library.com">hello@peptide-library.com</a>
      </p>

      <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-white/70">
        Peptide Library launched in January 2026.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
